02/10/2002
TIRANA, Albania -- Italian Defence Minister Antonio Martino is vowing to support Albania's integration into the EU. He met Tuesday (1 October) with Albanian President Alfred Moisiu in Tirana to discuss forms of co-operation in the military sector. "Italy will support Albania towards the road of integration with European structures, as it is considered a very important country," said Martino. He also applauded the recently improved political consensus in Albania for integration into NATO and the EU structures as well as efforts against illegal trafficking.
In other news, Dhame Pite, the deputy governor of Albania's National Bank, has been arrested on corruption charges. Newspaper reports suggest the arrest may be related to improperly awarding a contract to a French company to print the country's banknotes. (Albanian News, ATA, AP, AFP - 01/10/02)
